pageContext.claim: “Gregg Jarrett: 'Mueller’s prosecutors knew the “Dossier” was the product of bias and deception.” It was a Fake, just like so much news coverage in our Country. Nothing but a Witch Hunt, from beginning to end!'”
pageContext.analysis: The dossier commissioned by Fusion GPS for Democrats contained salacious elements and many details turned out to be incorrect or unproven. Fusion has said the former British spy who wrote it received $168,000. The FBI was sufficiently impressed that it considered pay him for additional research.The Fact Checker compared the Steele memos with the findings of the Mueller report and found several areas of overlap as well as major sections that remain unconfirmed and in doubt. Trump repeatedly claims the Russia investigation is "fake" but the information on Russian efforts to sway the 2016 election was developed by the intelligence community and published in a declassified report, in which the agencies said they had "high confidence" it was correct. three former campaign advisors have been charged as well as the president's former National Security Advisor. Investigators have not completed their investigation.
